229
00:16:11,577 --> 00:16:16,693
As a matter of fact, an informer in his group found out that he was leaving

230
00:16:16,693 --> 00:16:27,659
but without a definite date and he did something that cancelled that informer's information.

231
00:16:27,659 --> 00:16:30,772
In any rate, we're glad that he's here.

232
00:16:30,772 --> 00:16:32,666
So, we headed for Canada

233
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:39,140
and Ismail Barkat, most of you know him, he's a very hot-tempered, very loud, beautiful person,

234
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:39,965
we love him,

235
00:16:39,965 --> 00:16:43,187
and he was supposed to meet us in Seattle.

236
00:16:43,187 --> 00:16:47,356
And he swears he was there at 1:30

237
00:16:47,356 --> 00:16:50,532
and we were there at 1:00 o'clock and we waited until 3:00 o'clock.

238
00:16:50,532 --> 00:16:56,343
And according to his account and our account, we existed in the same place, but we never saw each other,

239
00:16:56,343 --> 00:16:57,567
We never heard each other

240
00:16:57,567 --> 00:17:01,856
as loud as he is. He said...

241
00:17:01,856 --> 00:17:06,241
he said I even took the public address system and I called you,

242
00:17:06,241 --> 00:17:07,786
we didn't hear a thing.

243
00:17:07,786 --> 00:17:10,395
We didn't see him. We didn't hear him. He didn't see us

244
00:17:10,395 --> 00:17:12,872
and there was nothing.

245
00:17:12,872 --> 00:17:15,371
Anyway, so, we waited until the next day

246
00:17:15,371 --> 00:17:19,230
when Raymond... no... Ismail went back to Seattle

247
00:17:19,230 --> 00:17:23,440
and I had nothing to do, so I tried to smuggle Dr. Mansour into Canada.

248
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:26,632
It didn't work out.

249
00:17:27,926 --> 00:17:32,445
I rented a car, went to the border and usually they let you pass, you know,

250
00:17:32,445 --> 00:17:36,444
because the guy at the post said "where are you from?" I said Tucson, Arizona.

251
00:17:36,444 --> 00:17:38,024
He said "can I see some IDs?"

252
00:17:38,024 --> 00:17:41,933
I said "oh, oh, OK. So, we're gonna turn around..."

253
00:17:44,044 --> 00:17:46,365
So, meantime, Ismail went back to Canada

254
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:52,370
and Raymond Catton went with us in the morning to the Canadian Consulate

255
00:17:52,370 --> 00:17:59,763
where we found out that we have to have five-day mandatory waiting period for an Egyptian to get a visa.

256
00:17:59,763 --> 00:18:07,834
However, the vice counsel, a lady, turned out to be from Raymond Catton's old country's village,

257
00:18:07,834 --> 00:18:10,017
a small village, it's called Lancashire

258
00:18:10,017 --> 00:18:13,085
in England, and they spoke the same language.

259
00:18:13,085 --> 00:18:16,078
You know, this is how they knew each other.

260
00:18:16,078 --> 00:18:21,193
"Good morning, (imitating the Lancashire dialect),"

261
00:18:21,193 --> 00:18:24,229
and she said "good morning (imitating the response in the Lancashire dialect)"

262
00:18:24,229 --> 00:18:26,913
and he said "oh, you're from Lancashire."

263
00:18:26,913 --> 00:18:30,706
And she said "that's right."

264
00:18:30,706 --> 00:18:33,415
She said "ok. Here's the visa."

265
00:18:33,415 --> 00:18:34,978
Free.

266
00:18:34,978 --> 00:18:41,106
I mean, if Ismail Barakat went with us, first we would have ended up in jail

267
00:18:41,106 --> 00:18:42,167
because he's loud.

268
00:18:44,312 --> 00:18:48,224
He will never go back to Vancouver without this man.

269
00:18:48,224 --> 00:18:53,366
He's Dr. Mansour's best friend

270
00:18:53,366 --> 00:19:00,553
And had they mentioned that you cannot have a visa to enter Canada,

271
00:19:00,553 --> 00:19:02,616
I mean, Barakat would have destroyed the Consulate,

272
00:19:02,616 --> 00:19:06,628
I'm telling you, we would have ended up... thank God we just didn't see him

273
00:19:06,628 --> 00:19:07,766
and he didn't see us.

274
00:19:10,797 --> 00:19:13,767
So, with all these delays,

275
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:16,450
we made it to the Friday prayer in Vancouver. 

276
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:21,003
And we went immediately after, after the KHUTBA

277
00:19:21,003 --> 00:19:24,664
and they just finished the KHUTBA and the prayer, so we sat with them

278
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:26,957
and they all cancelled going back to work

279
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:28,779
and we sat until 4 o'clock,

280
00:19:28,779 --> 00:19:32,324
from about 2 o'clock to 4 o'clock. 

281
00:19:32,324 --> 00:19:35,711
And we got to talk to them and 

282
00:19:35,711 --> 00:19:40,004
we discussed a lot of things. We did exactly everything we wanted to do 

283
00:19:40,004 --> 00:19:41,917
and the Friday prayer.

284
00:19:41,917 --> 00:19:46,608
And then we had meetings on Friday night, Saturday night and Sunday night

285
00:19:46,608 --> 00:19:48,313
in three different places

286
00:19:48,313 --> 00:19:52,203
about fifty or sixty people and everything was just fantastic.

287
00:19:52,203 --> 00:19:55,041
The objectors of the past didn't even show up.

288
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:56,296
There were no more objections.

289
00:19:56,296 --> 00:20:05,860
And what I carried to them is the new profound conclusion that we all must have... that "God is doing everything."

290
00:20:09,503 --> 00:20:18,176
So, as you can tell, we'll be talking about these things for the next few weeks Insha Allah

291
00:20:18,176 --> 00:20:20,590
and we may discuss more details tonight

292
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:24,675
and you will get a chance to greet Dr. Mansour.

293
00:20:24,675 --> 00:20:27,551
We're glad, we're glad he's here.

294
00:20:27,551 --> 00:20:31,923
And it is a tremendous victory.

295
00:20:33,898 --> 00:20:35,274
So, it is time to quit.

296
00:20:35,274 --> 00:20:36,219
AQEM AL-SALAT.

297
00:20:36,219 --> 00:20:39,036
ALLAH-O AKBAR, ALLAH-O AKBAR.


